# Camera & OCR Integration

## Camera Setup (CameraX 1.5.3)
- Use `AndroidView` for CameraX Preview in Compose
- Handle lifecycle properly with `LocalLifecycleOwner`
- Request `CAMERA` permission before access with proper rationale
- Provide proper error handling and fallbacks
- CameraX dependencies: core, camera2, lifecycle, view, extensions

```kotlin
@Composable
fun CameraPreview(
    onImageCaptured: (Bitmap) -> Unit,
    onError: (Exception) -> Unit,
    modifier: Modifier = Modifier
) {
    val context = LocalContext.current
    val lifecycleOwner = LocalLifecycleOwner.current
    
    AndroidView(
        factory = { ctx ->
            PreviewView(ctx).apply {
                // CameraX setup with lifecycle binding
            }
        },
        modifier = modifier
    )
}
```

## Camera Configuration
- Optimize image quality for OCR (good lighting, focus)
- Support flash, focus, and exposure controls
- Provide card overlay guides (16:9, 4:3, 3:4, credit card aspect ratios) via `CardOverlay`
- Allow preview and retake before confirming via `ImagePreview`
- Capture both front and back images (front-first flow with skip option for back)
- Use `CaptureButton` for consistent capture UI
- Handle camera errors via `CameraError` component

## Camera Components (in `presentation/components/camera/`)
- `CameraPreview.kt` — Main camera preview composable
- `CaptureButton.kt` — Styled capture button with animation
- `CardOverlay.kt` — Card-shaped overlay guide for framing
- `ImagePreview.kt` — Post-capture image review
- `CameraPermission.kt` / `CameraPermissionComponent.kt` — Permission handling
- `CameraManager.kt` — Camera lifecycle management
- `CameraError.kt` — Error display and retry UI

## OCR Processing (ML Kit 16.0.1 — Bundled Offline)
**CRITICAL**: OCR is ONLY for Credit/Debit cards — never for other card types!

### When to Use OCR
- ✅ `CardType.Credit` selected → Run OCR
- ✅ `CardType.Debit` selected → Run OCR
- ❌ Transport, Gift, Voucher, Membership, etc. → NO OCR
- Check via `cardType.supportsOCR()` method

### OCR Implementation
Two classes handle OCR:
- `MLKitTextRecognizer` — Wraps ML Kit `TextRecognition.getClient()`
- `CardTextParser` — Parses raw OCR text into structured card fields

```kotlin
class MLKitTextRecognizer @Inject constructor() {
    private val recognizer = TextRecognition.getClient(TextRecognizerOptions.DEFAULT_OPTIONS)
    
    suspend fun extractCardData(bitmap: Bitmap): OCRResult = suspendCoroutine { continuation ->
        val image = InputImage.fromBitmap(bitmap, 0)
        recognizer.process(image)
            .addOnSuccessListener { visionText ->
                val data = CardTextParser.parseCardText(visionText.text)
                continuation.resume(data)
            }
            .addOnFailureListener { exception ->
                continuation.resumeWithException(exception)
            }
    }
}
```

### Extraction Patterns (via `CardTextParser`)
- **Card Number**: 15-16 digits (Visa, Mastercard, Amex) — validated with Luhn algorithm
- **Expiry Date**: MM/YY or MM/YYYY format
- **CVV**: 3-4 digits
- **Cardholder Name**: Text in UPPERCASE
- **Bank Name**: Optional extraction

### OCR Data Keys (from `Card.companion`)
```kotlin
const val CARD_NUMBER_KEY = "cardNumber"
const val EXPIRY_DATE_KEY = "expiryDate"
const val CARDHOLDER_NAME_KEY = "cardholderName"
const val CVV_KEY = "cvv"
const val BANK_NAME_KEY = "bankName"
```

### OCR UI Components
- `OCRStatusCard` — Shows OCR processing state (scanning, success, failure)
- `ManualEntryCard` — Fallback UI for manual data entry when OCR fails

## Image Storage
- Store captured images in app's private storage via `ImageFileManager`
- Compress images before saving (JPEG quality 85)
- Naming convention: `{cardId}_front.jpg`, `{cardId}_back.jpg`
- Clean up orphaned images when cards are deleted
- Use Coil for efficient image loading with placeholders

## Permission Handling
```kotlin
val cameraPermissionState = rememberPermissionState(
    android.Manifest.permission.CAMERA
)

LaunchedEffect(cameraPermissionState) {
    if (!cameraPermissionState.status.isGranted) {
        cameraPermissionState.launchPermissionRequest()
    }
}
```

## Error Handling
- Handle camera initialization failures gracefully
- Handle OCR processing failures — always offer manual input fallback
- Provide user-friendly error messages via `CameraError` component
- Offer retry mechanisms
- Never crash on permission denial

## Best Practices
- ✅ Run OCR on background thread (via coroutines)
- ✅ Show processing indicator during OCR
- ✅ Provide manual input option as fallback
- ✅ Validate extracted data with patterns and Luhn algorithm
- ✅ Clean up camera resources properly on lifecycle changes
- ✅ Use `ProcessCardImageUseCase` for OCR business logic
- ❌ Don't run OCR on non-Credit/Debit cards
- ❌ Don't block UI during processing
- ❌ Don't save raw bitmaps — compress first
- ❌ Don't forget to handle camera lifecycle
- ❌ Don't log extracted card data (sensitive information)
